The President chaired a meeting with his national security team to discuss ongoing efforts to mitigate terrorist threats and enhance national security leading into the anniversary of 9/11. The President praised coordination and information sharing among federal, state, and local officials. He directed his team to pursue threat information and maintain a heightened state of vigilance. The President emphasized the importance of not relaxing counterterrorism efforts in the weeks and months following the anniversary. Attendees at the meeting included various government officials such as the Attorney General, Secretary of Homeland Security, Chief of Staff, National Security Advisor, Director of the FBI, and Director of the CIA. The President requested regular updates on security preparations and developments related to recent threat information.